Sec. 103.52. (A) As used in sections 103.52 and 103.53 of 7
the Revised Code: 8
(1) "JLEOC" means the joint law enforcement oversight 9
committee created under this section. 10
(2) "Peace officer" has the meaning defined in section 11
109.71 of the Revised Code. 12
(B) The joint law enforcement oversight committee (JLEOC) 13
is created. JLEOC shall evaluate training standards and programs 14
required to be completed by any peace officer in the state. 15
(C) JLEOC shall consist of the following members: 16
(1) Three members of the senate appointed by the president 17

