Sec. 103.53. (A) JLEOC shall do both of the following : 89
(1) Review and evaluate training standards and programs 90
required to be completed by any peace officer in the state; 91
(2) Recommend, to the extent JLEOC determines appropriate, 92
improvements in statutes and rules concerning peace officer 93
training standards and programs. 94
(B) JLEOC may do all of the following: 95
(1) Require that the chairperson of the Ohio peace officer 96
training commission appear before JLEOC to provide information 97
and answer questions about the activities of the Ohio peace 98
officer training commission; 99
(2) Review bills and resolutions regarding the peace 100
officer training standards and programs that are introduced in 101
the general assembly. JLEOC may submit a report of its review of 102
a bill or resolution to the general assembly in accordance with 103
section 101.68 of the Revised Code. The report may include 104
JLEOC's determination regarding the bill's or resolution's 105
desirability as a matter of public policy; JLEOC's decision on 106

